<br>
then i found one closer after about 6 months. i think it was lutheran...and i told my family so it was better.<br>
<br>
i havent really joined a denomination...i dont like that they even exist. it was confusing to me. even the non denominations churches still seem like a denomination. <br>
<br>
so i go to any of them depending where i am.<br>
<br>
its not been really easy. i think because i still carry traditions from the culture i'm from and to people who dont know anything about it...they can be quick to think its 'not christian', when its really just not what they do. <br>
<br>
i like some of the ceremony from catholic churches i've been to....and i liked the 'freedom' of the non denoms also. i even went to a temple to see what that was like. not to go to try to worship jesus, but to see the traditions of the jewish people. i actually had some good talks with some people. <br>
<br>
in the east here i've been going to a non denom type church for a year or so more often then anyplace else.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#DEB887><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bsparrowshearth.showUserPublicProfile?gid=peaches116>peaches116</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Dreamer</span><br>  Posts: 229<br> <font color=#B87333>(8/2/03 11:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fsparrowshearthfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25.topic&index=18>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.onerefuge.com/7HJavatar4.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Denominations: Your history?</span><hr size=1> WOW!  70 miles is a long ways to drive everyr week for church!  That must have been one really great church! <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center">**********************************************<br>
